## Instructions

1. Execute the Five-Phase ReAct Loop from your system prompt.
2. **Auto-scope inference:** If `review_scope` is `full` (or unspecified) AND every file in `files_to_review` is a `.tsx` file under `frontend/components/`, infer `review_scope="ui_component_pr"` and record the inference in `validation_log[0]` (e.g., `"Auto-inferred review_scope=ui_component_pr from file mix"`).
3. Run deterministic tools first for FD1, FD3, FD5, FD6, and the AST-detectable FD2/FD7 hypotheses on every applicable file. Apply LLM judgment only for residual FD2 (B6 Route Handler hygiene, U1 RSC suitability) and FD4 appropriateness (always recorded as `gaps`, never findings).
4. Produce a certificate for every hypothesis tested.
5. Apply the Judge criteria (Section 7) to filter findings.
6. Apply the strictest verdict decision rules (Section 8). Auto-reject anti-patterns (FE-AP-4, FE-AP-6, FE-AP-7, FE-AP-12, FE-AP-18, FE-AP-19) and critical FD3 hypotheses (`CSP1`, `CSP2`, `SBX2`, `SEC1`, `SEC2`, `TRUST1`, `TRUST2`) take precedence over count thresholds. List any auto-reject reasons inline at the top of the `statement` field.
7. Output a single `ReviewReport` JSON object as your final response.
